<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-6158] Missing directory entries in groovy-all JAR</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-6158</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Checking groovy-all jar content via any zip tool.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I expect:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;groovy/beans
groovy/beans/Bindable.class
...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I get:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;groovy/beans/Bindable.class
...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;e.g, all entries for directories are not packaged in the jar. This causes a problem while trying to get groovy resources from classpath:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://bugs.sun.com/view_bug.do?bug_id=4761949&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://bugs.sun.com/view_bug.do?bug_id=4761949&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;In particular, it breaks Spock integration with Arquillian:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/ARQ-1143&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/ARQ-1143&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
